  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-DOC-05, add a Tags filter to the Documents PCF command bar consuming the shared `TagFilter` component from `@spaarke/ui-components` (task 010 + 012). Option source: `sprk_documenttype` choice values via existing `DataverseMetadataService.fetchOptionSet('sprk_documenttype')`. Sort alphabetically. Selection semantics: **OR** — document matches if its `documentType` ∈ selected set. Active-filters chip row renders below the command bar when ≥1 selected: `Filtered by: [Type1 ×] [Type2 ×] … Clear all`. Footer count reflects filtered results: e.g., "Showing 5 of 31 documents · filtered by 2 tags". The existing FilterPanel "Document Type" dropdown is RELOCATED to this command-bar Tags filter (not duplicated). Underlying field is unchanged.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior frontend developer with Fluent UI v9 + Dataverse option-set fetch experience. Familiar with `@spaarke/ui-components` `TagFilter` contract (task 010), `DataverseMetadataService.fetchOptionSet`, and the Semantic Search PCF filter/footer architecture.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SemanticSearchControl.tsx` exposes `selectedTags: string[]` state. Tags filter consumes the shared `TagFilter` with `sortAlphabetical: true` and options sourced from `DataverseMetadataService.fetchOptionSet('sprk_documenttype')` (memoized — fetched once per mount). OR-match filtering applied to result set (filtered AFTER backend response, before render). Footer count reflects filtered result. Existing FilterPanel "Document Type" dropdown REMOVED (or hidden behind a feature flag for safe rollback). PCF builds clean. Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-DOC-05 relocates the existing Document Type filter from the sidebar `FilterPanel` to the command bar using the new shared `TagFilter` component (task 010). The option set itself (`sprk_documenttype`) is unchanged — only the UI surface moves. OR-semantics is per Owner Clarifications row 3 (existing filter behavior). Active-tags chip row + footer count are new affordances driven by `TagFilter`'s `selected.length`. This task lays groundwork for FR-DOC-06 (task 043) which removes the sidebar entirely and moves the remaining filters into the command bar.
    </background>
