  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check">Verify context &lt; 60%. If higher, run `context-handoff` before proceeding.</step>
    <step order="0.5" name="Invoke fluent-v9-component">Invoke `Skill fluent-v9-component` (binding per design.md §6.0). Load `fluent-v9-component-authoring.md`, `fluent-v9-theming.md`.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Load knowledge">Read ADR-006, ADR-012, ADR-021, ADR-022, ADR-028; PCF CLAUDE.md. Read `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`, `FilterPanel.tsx` (note Document Type dropdown location), `DataverseMetadataService.ts` (confirm `fetchOptionSet` signature). Verify task 012 has exported `TagFilter` from the barrel.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Fetch option set on mount">In `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`, add `useEffect` to call `DataverseMetadataService.fetchOptionSet('sprk_documenttype')` once on mount. Store as `tagOptions: TagFilterOption[]` state (map `{value, label}`).</step>
    <step order="3" name="Add selectedTags state">Add `selectedTags: string[]` state to `SemanticSearchControl.tsx`. Initialize empty.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Render TagFilter in command bar">Import `TagFilter` from `@spaarke/ui-components`. Render in the command bar with `options={tagOptions}`, `selected={selectedTags}`, `onChange={setSelectedTags}`, `label="Tags"`, `sortAlphabetical={true}`. The component auto-renders chip row + Clear all when `selected.length &gt;= 1`.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Apply OR-filter to result set">In the render path (or `useMemo` over `results`), filter: `selectedTags.length === 0 ? results : results.filter(r =&gt; selectedTags.includes(r.documentType))`. OR-semantics emerges naturally from `.includes`.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Footer count update">Update the footer count string: when `selectedTags.length === 0`, show "Showing N documents"; when `&gt; 0`, show "Showing X of Y documents · filtered by N tags".</step>
    <step order="7" name="Remove FilterPanel Document Type dropdown">In `FilterPanel.tsx`, remove the Document Type dropdown (it is RELOCATED, not duplicated, per spec). Verify no other consumer references the removed dropdown. NOTE: the sidebar FilterPanel itself is removed/hidden in task 043 (FR-DOC-06) — here we only remove the Document Type element.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Dark-mode + a11y check">Run PCF in dev harness with `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme`. Verify Tags filter trigger, menu, chip row, footer count text use v9 tokens. Run axe scan.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Build verification">Run `npm run build:prod` from PCF root.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">Invoke `Skill code-review` then `Skill adr-check`. Resolve all findings.</step>
    <step order="10" name="Checkpoint">Run `context-handoff` (silent: ✅ Checkpoint).</step>
    <step order="11" name="Update task tracking">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 042 status 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to next pending task (043).</step>
  </steps>

